ctDAWanDeviceNumDevices.name: ctDAWanDeviceNumDevices
ctDAWanDeviceNumDevices.description: This is the total number of devices currently in the local system cache.

ctDAWanDevicesTable.name: ctDAWanDevicesTable
ctDAWanDevicesTable.description: A list of Demand Access remote WAN devices. This list reflects the contents of the local system cache. The local cache maintains an account for each device. Each entry in the local cache is a conceptual row in the SNMP table.

ctDAWanDeviceEntry.name: ctDAWanDeviceEntry
ctDAWanDeviceEntry.description: An entry containing wan device information and statistics.

ctDAWanDeviceIndex.name: ctDAWanDeviceIndex
ctDAWanDeviceIndex.description: This is the index into this table. This index uniquely identifies the device.

ctDAWanDeviceIfIndex.name: ctDAWanDeviceIfIndex
ctDAWanDeviceIfIndex.description: This is the ifIndex value of the wan connection group. If the ifIndex value is unknown, the value of this object will be zero.

ctDAWanDeviceSessionID.name: ctDAWanDeviceSessionID
ctDAWanDeviceSessionID.description: This is the unique identifier of the last session when a wan device was in the active state.

ctDAWanDeviceState.name: ctDAWanDeviceState
ctDAWanDeviceState.description: This is the state of the device.

ctDAWanDeviceDescr.name: ctDAWanDeviceDescr
ctDAWanDeviceDescr.description: A textual string that identifies the peer device.

ctDAWanDeviceConnectControl.name: ctDAWanDeviceConnectControl
ctDAWanDeviceConnectControl.description: This object controls the desired state of the wan device. Setting this object to connect(1) will initiate the set of actions to bring the wan device to the active state. Only set the object to connect(1) when the current value of ctDAWanDeviceState is inactive. Setting this object to disconnect(2) will initiate the set of actions to bring the wan device to the inactive state. Only set this object to disconnect(2) when the ctDAWanDeviceState is active. After setting the device to connect(1) or disconnect(2), refer to ctDAWanDeviceState to determine the state of the wan device. Queries to ctDAWanDeviceConnectControl return unknown results.

ctDAWanDeviceConnectType.name: ctDAWanDeviceConnectType
ctDAWanDeviceConnectType.description: This specifies the type of the wan connection.

ctDAWanDeviceL2Encapsulation.name: ctDAWanDeviceL2Encapsulation
ctDAWanDeviceL2Encapsulation.description: This is the type of layer 2 encapsulation used when connecting to this device.

ctDAWanDeviceNumConnections.name: ctDAWanDeviceNumConnections
ctDAWanDeviceNumConnections.description: This is the current number of wan connections to this device.

ctDAWanDeviceCurrentBandwidth.name: ctDAWanDeviceCurrentBandwidth
ctDAWanDeviceCurrentBandwidth.description: This is the aggregate bandwidth of all current connections.

ctDAWanDeviceInitialBandwidth.name: ctDAWanDeviceInitialBandwidth
ctDAWanDeviceInitialBandwidth.description: This is the desired initial bandwidth in bits per second used when calling this peer object. The system will bring up enough connections to meet the bandwidth requirement. The value only represents dial type connections. It does not include leased circuits.

ctDAWanDeviceMaxBandwidth.name: ctDAWanDeviceMaxBandwidth
ctDAWanDeviceMaxBandwidth.description: This is the maximum amount of bandwidth in bits per seconde used when calling this peer wan device object. This value only represents dial type connections. It does not include leased line circuits.

ctDAWanDeviceH0Support.name: ctDAWanDeviceH0Support
ctDAWanDeviceH0Support.description: Indicates whether an H0 connection can be used when calling this peer wan device object.

ctDAWanDeviceChargedUnits.name: ctDAWanDeviceChargedUnits
ctDAWanDeviceChargedUnits.description: The total number of charging units applying to this peer device since this row was created. Only the charging units applying to the local interface,i.e. for originated calls or for calls with 'Reverse charging' being active, will be counted here.

ctDAWanDeviceSuccessCalls.name: ctDAWanDeviceSuccessCalls
ctDAWanDeviceSuccessCalls.description: Number of completed calls to this peer device.

ctDAWanDeviceFailCalls.name: ctDAWanDeviceFailCalls
ctDAWanDeviceFailCalls.description: Number of failed call attempts to this peer device since the row was created.

ctDAWanDeviceAcceptCalls.name: ctDAWanDeviceAcceptCalls
ctDAWanDeviceAcceptCalls.description: Number of calls from this peer device accepted since the row was created.

ctDAWanDeviceRefuseCalls.name: ctDAWanDeviceRefuseCalls
ctDAWanDeviceRefuseCalls.description: Number of calls from this peer device refused since the row was created.

ctDAWanDeviceConnectTime.name: ctDAWanDeviceConnectTime
ctDAWanDeviceConnectTime.description: The value of sysUpTime at the time when the device entered its current active state. This object will be 0 if the device is currently inactive. This object will be upctDAted whenever there is a state transition to the active state.

ctDAWanDeviceConnectDirection.name: ctDAWanDeviceConnectDirection
ctDAWanDeviceConnectDirection.description: The direction from which the last connect occurred.

ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectTime.name: ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectTime
ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the last call to this peer device was disconnected. This object will be upctDAted whenever a call is disconnected.

ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectDirection.name: ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectDirection
ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectDirection.description: The direction from which the last disconnect occurred.

ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectCause.name: ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectCause
ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectCause.description: The encoded network cause value associated with the last call. This object will be upctDAted whenever a call is started or cleared. The value of this object will depend on the interface type as well as on the protocol and protocol version being used on this interface.

ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectText.name: ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectText
ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectText.description: ASCII text describing the reason for the last call termination. This object exists because it would be impossible for a management station to store all possible cause values for all types of interfaces. It should be used only if a management station is unable to decode the value of ctDAWanDeviceLastDisconnectCause. This object will be upctDAted whenever a call is started or cleared.

ctDAWanTNListTable.name: ctDAWanTNListTable
ctDAWanTNListTable.description: A list of telephone numbers accessible to the wan device.

ctDAWanTNListEntry.name: ctDAWanTNListEntry
ctDAWanTNListEntry.description: An entry containing a telephone number.

ctDAWanTNListIndex.name: ctDAWanTNListIndex
ctDAWanTNListIndex.description: This is the index into this table. This index uniquely identifies the telephone number.

ctDAWanTN.name: ctDAWanTN
ctDAWanTN.description: This is a telephone number for this wan device.
